<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>81997</id>
	<title>PRINTING: formatting options for headers and footers</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Remark: Actually, the "bug" (why is it called a bug if I am filing an enhancement request??)</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">hasn't appeared with a certain version, because it isn't a bug, just a lacking feature.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">Problem description: 
Headers and footers in spreadsheets cannot be formatted the same way as in LO Writer.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">It is especially annoying that the only internationally accepted way of writing a date (ISO8601, which should be the default anywhere and everywhere in LO, but it isn't) cannot be chosen for a date in headers and footers, only in cells.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Steps to reproduce:</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.2">1 format, page</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.3">2 header (or footer, for that matter)</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.4">3 edit</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.5">4 put cursor in one of the three fields</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.6">5 click the last but one button to insert the date</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.7">6 OK</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.8">7 print the page</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.9">8 get annoyed by the date in non-8601 format</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Current behavior:
date cannot be formatted AND the default is not the ISO standard</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">Expected behavior:
date can be formatted (like in cells and in footers of LO Writer) AND ISO standard is the default</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="6">
			<sentence id="6.1">Operating System: All
Version: 4.2.4.2 release</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
